<%# How it works — plain-English docs for the recommender. Signal statuses
    render from src/signals.js (shared with the home-page grid). %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { title: 'How it works' }) %>
</head>
<body class="min-h-screen bg-paper font-sans text-ink antialiased">
  <%- include('partials/frame') %>
  <%- include('partials/nav') %>

  <main class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl overflow-hidden px-6 py-12">
    <span class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-10 top-6 select-none font-serif text-[15rem] font-extrabold leading-none text-ink/[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">仕</span>

    <div class="reveal relative">
      <h1>
        <span class="relative inline-block font-serif text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">
          <span class="absolute -inset-x-4 -inset-y-1.5 rotate-1 bg-sakura" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="relative text-paper">仕組み</span>
        </span>
        <span class="jp-sub mt-3">shikumi — how your recommendations are made</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        <p>
          OtakuGuide doesn't guess from genres alone. Every anime's synopsis —
          from two independent sources, MyAnimeList's fan-prose and Wikipedia's
          encyclopedic plot section — is converted into a <strong>384-number
          fingerprint</strong> (an <em>embedding</em>) by a small language model
          running locally. Anime that <em>mean</em> similar things end up with
          similar fingerprints, even when they share no tags at all.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you open an anime's page, the engine measures the angle between
          its fingerprint and all <span class="tabular-nums">38,000+</span>
          others (<em>cosine similarity</em> — closer angle, closer story).
          That's signal 01. Signal 02 compares community tags, weighted so
          rare, specific tags ("iyashikei", "time loop") count far more than
          ubiquitous ones ("action"). Each signal votes, the votes are
          normalized to a common scale, and a weighted sum produces the final
          ranking — the <span class="text-sakura">赤い糸</span> list you see.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every recommendation says which signals matched — if it can't explain
          itself, it doesn't ship. Eight signals vote today; the remaining
          four join as their data lands. Same math, more voters.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# ——— The twelve, with honest status ——— %>
      <h2 class="mt-14">
        <span class="font-serif text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">十二の信号</span>
        <span class="jp-sub">juuni no shingou — the twelve signals</span>
      </h2>

      <%# `signals` comes from src/signals.js via the route — the single
          source of truth shared with the home-page grid. %>
      <ol class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-px border border-ink/15 bg-ink/15 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <% signals.forEach((s, i) => { %>
        <li class="bg-paper p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
            <p class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
              <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30"><%= String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0') %></span>
              <span class="meta"><%= s.name %></span>
            </p>
            <% if (s.status === 'live') { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 bg-sakura px-1.5 py-0.5 text-paper">live</span>
            <% } else if (s.status === 'ready') { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 border border-ink/50 px-1.5 py-0.5">ready</span>
            <% } else { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 text-ink/40"><%= s.status %></span>
            <% } %>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink/70"><%= s.blurb %></p>
        </li>
        <% }) %>
      </ol>

      <p class="meta mt-8">model — minilm-l6-v2, 384 dimensions, runs locally · math — cosine similarity, min-max normalization, weighted sum · nothing leaves your machine</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
